ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: What are your impressions of your activity partner's: Attractiveness
What are your impressions of your activity partner's: Awkwardness
What are your impressions of your activity partner's: Intelligence
What are your impressions of your activity partner's: Likeability
What are your impressions of your activity partner's: Trustworthiness
My partner in this activity seems to be.... (submissive/dominant)
How willing would you be to live near your partner from this activity?
Notes: 0=Not at all willing; 1=A little willing; 2=Somewhat willing; 3=Very willing

ElementDescription: How likely would you be to hang out in your free time with your partner from this activity?
Notes: 0=Not at all likely; 1=A little likely; 2=Somewhat likely; 3=Very likely

ElementDescription: How comfortable would you be to sit next to your partner from this activity?
Notes: 0=Not at all comfortable; 1=A little comfortable; 2=Somewhat comfortable; 3=Very comfortable

ElementDescription: How likely would you be to start a conversation with your partner from this activity?
Notes: 0=Not at all likely; 1=A little likely; 2=Somewhat likely; 3=Very likely
